{"block1":"<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Many arthritis sufferers are turning to natural ways to treat their arthritis symptoms.&nbsp; Whether this is because of the high cost of conventional drugs, or because they come with harmful side effects, they are choosing the natural route.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are a number of home remedies that are very effective in <a href=\"http:\/\/jointreport.net\/joint-information\/how-arthritis-can-be-treated\/\"  >treating an arthritis<\/a> condition and its symptoms.&nbsp;You can purchase home remedy books on the internet, in book stores, and in most health stores, to help you choose the right method of treatment for you.&nbsp; Because of the long list of natural treatments available for treating your arthritis symptoms, we will take a look at just a few here.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"\/images\/photo-of-a-woman-preparing-for-epsom-salt-bath.jpg\" class=\"img_left \" alt=\"photo of a woman preparing for epsom salt bath\" style=\"float: left; padding: 8px; padding-left: 0;\" \/><\/h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Cold weather always seems to&nbsp;take a toll on an arthritis sufferer.&nbsp; When you hear, &ldquo;chilled to the bone,&rdquo; that is what it feels like to an arthritis sufferer; the cold causes the bones to ache and become painful.&nbsp; In such a situation, the home remedy of soaking in an Epsom salt bath feels even better.&nbsp; Not only will the bath warm the bones;&nbsp;the Epsom salts help relieve pain, and&nbsp;it actually draws out the pain while you are soaking.&nbsp; This remedy isn&rsquo;t just for the winter months, though, it can be used anytime of the year.&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Massaging hot vinegar in an aching joint can relieve joint pain.&nbsp; For the best results in keeping pain away,&nbsp;do this daily.&nbsp; Another good massaging agent for relieving arthritis symptoms is a warm olive oil body rub.&nbsp; Not only is this soothing, especially if done by your sweetheart, it relieves arthritis pain.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Adding ginger to your cooking can reduce arthritis symptoms.&nbsp; You can also drink ginger tea or green tea, both of&nbsp;which can reduce inflammation in the joint, lessening joint pain.&nbsp; Certain supplements can help cure your arthritis. For example,&nbsp;Omega 3 fish oils are good for treating the inflammation <a href=\"arthritis-causes\"  >caused by arthritis<\/a>.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"\/images\/photo-of-different-beta-cryptoxanthin-food.jpg\" class=\"img_right \" alt=\"photo of different Beta-Cryptoxanthin food\" style=\"float: right; padding: 8px; padding-right: 0;\" \/><\/h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Detoxifying the body can help to cure&nbsp;arthritis symptoms.&nbsp; Dandelion increases the frequency of&nbsp;urination,&nbsp; and removes fluids from the body.&nbsp; A build up of fluids can cause inflammation, so by removing these fluids you reduce inflammation, and bring relief to&nbsp;your arthritis symptoms.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Eating more fruits and vegetables is helpful for&nbsp;arthritis sufferers.&nbsp; There are a number of fruits and vegetables that are high in Beta-Cryptoxanthin which is great for the bones and cartilage.&nbsp; These include berries, squash, pineapple, and grapefruit.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A low-impact daily exercise routine can improve your mobility, strengthen your joints and improve your overall health.&nbsp; Low impact exercise includes&nbsp;swimming or walking for thirty minutes a day.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">These are just a few ways to use home remedies to cure your arthritis symptoms.&nbsp;&nbsp; Before starting or stopping a treatment, always speak with a healthcare professional.&nbsp; He or she will be able to guide you in the proper treatment for your specific medical condition.&nbsp; Results from the use of home remedies vary among individuals just as in the use of conventional medicines.<\/p>\r\n"}